Police are looking for former Youth Enterprise Fund board member Clement Ayungo over allegations of hate speech.This follows a video clip shared on social which shows the aspirant saying he would lead protests if elections are rigged against Cord leader Raila Odinga.Ayungo is said to have incited residents of Ruaraka last week while campaigning for his MP bid."We will start with burning of cars at Ruaraka and then go to fight President Uhuru Kenyatta and his army. We are prepared for this election and Raila should not come telling us that he has lost, because he must win," he stated in the video.Police have asked the politician to surrender to the nearest police station for questioning.Ayungo's lawyers said they are meeting to agree on the date when the politician will be presented to police.Read: We will not allow hate speech to go unpunished